items.title: Beckham's homer lifts O's over Yanks in finale
items.summary: Tim Beckham hit a three-run homer to support Ubaldo Jimenez's 10-strikeout effort and the Orioles sent Sonny Gray to an early exit, avoiding a series sweep with a 6-4 victory over the Yankees on Sunday afternoon at Yankee Stadium.

items.title: Twins use 2 big frames to protect WC position
items.summary: The Twins erased an early five-run deficit with a pair of huge innings to power past the Blue Jays.

items.title: Crew wins behind Woodruff's start, 8-run 4th
items.summary: Where one rookie starter faltered, another stood strong. Brandon Woodruff put together seven solid innings in a critical series finale as the "road" Brewers knocked off the Marlins, 10-3, at Miller Park on Sunday. The clubs played in front of 24,535 fans as a total of 68,983 watched the three-game set, which was moved to Milwaukee in the wake of Hurricane Irma.
